## v1.2.0 (2026-06-15)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus planner idempotency fix (PR #1373, issue #1370)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Extended the `## When to Use` triggers: added planner-phase open-PR skip-gate
  and merged-closing-PR detection + issue-close triggers.
- Added 3 new `## Failed Attempts` rows:
  - Re-plan issue without checking for an existing open/merged closing PR → duplicate PRs + 5.5h churn
  - Search only open PRs for closing link → merged-closed issue re-implemented, never closes
  - Match PR to issue by assumed `{issue}-auto-impl` branch → fetch fails / wrong worktree
- Added `#### Planner skip-gate: call find_pr_for_issue before planning` subsection
  under Verified Workflow describing the unified planner/implementer skip semantics.
- Added `#### Merged closing-PR detection: find_merged_closing_pr` subsection
  covering `find_merged_closing_pr(issue)` and `gh issue close` flow.
- Added `#### Real head-branch resolution: always use get_pr_head_branch` subsection
  replacing assumed `{issue}-auto-impl` with `gh pr view headRefName`.
- Added new `## Verified On` row: ProjectHephaestus PR #1373 / issue #1370.
- Frontmatter: `version: "1.1.0"` → `"1.2.0"`, `date: 2026-06-10` → `2026-06-15`,
  new tags `planner-skip-gate`, `merged-closing-pr`, `find-merged-closing-pr`,
  `real-head-branch`, `assumed-branch-name`.
- Description: extended items with (10) planner open-PR skip-gate and
  (11) merged-closing-PR closes-open-issue triggers.

### Why

The automation-loop output.log (2026-06-15) burned ~5.5 hours opening duplicate
and zombie PRs for issue #1357 (and #1289/#1179) while a parallel PR #1358 had
already closed it. Three compounding root causes: (1) the PLANNER phase had no
open-PR skip-gate (the IMPLEMENTER phase already skipped issues with an existing
open PR but the PLANNER ran first and re-planned the same issue — wasting an
agent call and repeatedly failing on 529); (2) a MERGED closing-PR was not
recognized because discovery only searched `--state open`, so the issue stayed
open and got re-implemented; (3) the assumed branch name `{issue}-auto-impl` was
used to fetch a PR's head branch, which fails when the PR was filed from a
differently-named branch (e.g. `1179-auto-impl`). Fixes merged in PR #1373.

