## v1.1.0 (2026-06-10)

**What changed:** Widened the `_discover_failing_prs` except tuple from the
narrow `(json.JSONDecodeError, subprocess.CalledProcessError)` shown in the
v1.0.0 example to the canonical 4-tuple
`(subprocess.CalledProcessError, subprocess.TimeoutExpired, OSError,
json.JSONDecodeError)`. Added a new "Symmetric subprocess failure-mode
handling" section under Verified Workflow, a new Failed Attempts row for
narrow-tuple soft-fail, and a row in the Verified On table for PR #1097/#1151.

**Why it changed:** The example code in v1.0.0 caught only 2 of the 4
subprocess failure modes that a `gh`-wrapped helper can raise. A real
production incident (ProjectHephaestus issue #1096) showed that a `gh` CLI
hang (`subprocess.TimeoutExpired`) or a missing binary (`OSError` /
`FileNotFoundError`) propagated uncaught out of `_discover_failing_prs`,
got swallowed by the worker-thread exception handler, and marked the entire
work item failed — directly violating the docstring contract "Empty dict
on any lookup failure — discovery must never abort the drive." The fix
landed in PR #1097 (merged via PR #1151) with two regression tests. The
v1.0.0 example code in this skill is now a known-bad pattern that
reviewers would have copy-pasted into new helpers.

